datasets.name: 37d08591
datasets.query:
WITH storage_creds_cte AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT
    REGEXP_EXTRACT(credential, 'accessConnectors\/(.*?)\,mi_id') as access_credential,
    id,
    app_id
  FROM system.information_schema.storage_credentials
  LEFT JOIN slog.default.azure_application_details ON REGEXP_EXTRACT(credential, 'accessConnectors\/(.*?)\,mi_id') = display_name
)
SELECT
  subscription_id,
  resource_group,
  storage_account,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format,
  authType,
  authObjectId,
  storage_creds_cte.access_credential,
  userAgentHeader,
  CASE WHEN storage_creds_cte.access_credential IS NOT NULL THEN 'databricks' ELSE 'external' END requester,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN category = 'StorageWrite' THEN 1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS StorageWrite,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN category = 'StorageDelete' THEN 1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS StorageDelete,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN category = 'StorageRead' THEN 1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS StorageRead
FROM
  slog.default.azure_storage_logs
  LEFT JOIN storage_creds_cte ON authObjectId = storage_creds_cte.id
GROUP BY
  subscription_id,
  resource_group,
  storage_account,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format,
  authType,
  authObjectId,
  userAgentHeader,
  requester,
  storage_creds_cte.access_credential

datasets.name: 89a92a69
datasets.query:
WITH storage_creds_cte AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT
    REGEXP_EXTRACT(credential, 'accessConnectors\/(.*?)\,mi_id') as access_credential,
    id,
    app_id
  FROM system.information_schema.storage_credentials
  LEFT JOIN slog.default.azure_application_details ON REGEXP_EXTRACT(credential, 'accessConnectors\/(.*?)\,mi_id') = display_name
),
cte_details AS (
  SELECT
    subscription_id,
    resource_group,
    storage_account,
    table_catalog,
    table_schema,
    table_name,
    full_namespace,
    storage_path,
    table_type,
    data_source_format,
    authType,
    authObjectId,
    storage_creds_cte.access_credential,
    userAgentHeader,
    CASE WHEN storage_creds_cte.access_credential IS NOT NULL THEN 'databricks' ELSE 'external' END requester,
    category
  FROM
    slog.default.azure_storage_logs
    LEFT JOIN storage_creds_cte ON authObjectId = storage_creds_cte.id
)
SELECT
  subscription_id,
  resource_group,
  storage_account,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN
        category = "StorageRead"
        AND requester = 'external'
      THEN
        1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) as external_read,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN
        category = "StorageWrite"
        AND requester = 'external'
      THEN
        1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) as external_write,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN
        category = "StorageRead"
        AND requester = 'databricks'
      THEN
        1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) as uc_read,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN
        category = "StorageWrite"
        AND requester = 'databricks'
      THEN
        1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) as uc_write,
  CASE
    WHEN
      external_read > 0
      OR external_write > 0
    THEN
      'More Investigation Needed'
    WHEN
      external_read = 0
      OR external_write = 0
    THEN
      'Good Candidate For Managed Table'
  END AS recommendation
FROM
  cte_details
GROUP BY
  subscription_id,
  resource_group,
  storage_account,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format

widget.name: 1fa7d8d8
widget.textbox_spec:
# Table Migration Breakdown

This dashboard provides a high-level overview of both registered and unregistered tables, as well as how these tables are being accessed. External tables that are exclusively read and updated via Databricks Unity Catalog (UC) are ideal candidates for conversion to 'managed' tables. However, tables with external readers and writers require further investigation before being moved to ensure that other business processes are not disrupted.

Tables with the name 'foreign' are one where a specific registered table namespace could not be identified. This can happen due to pipeline authorization issues on a storage account, or the underlying table is only available in the storage account.
